# Privacy Policy for BrainWorkout

_Last updated: July 4, 2026_

Aymhi Consulting Corp. ("we," "us," or "our") operates the BrainWorkout mobile application (the "App"). This Privacy Policy explains what information the App collects, how it is used, and the choices you have. By using BrainWorkout, you agree to the practices described in this policy.

## Information We Do Not Collect

BrainWorkout does not require you to create an account or sign in, and we do not operate any servers that receive your gameplay data. Your high scores, daily streak, and app settings (such as theme and advanced mode) are stored only in local storage on your device and are never transmitted to us or to any third party.

## Information Collected by Third-Party Services

BrainWorkout is supported by advertising. To show ads, we use Google AdMob, and to manage your ad-related privacy choices we use the Google User Messaging Platform (UMP). These third-party services may automatically collect certain information when the App is used, which may include:

- Device identifiers (such as the Advertising Identifier / IDFA, only if you grant tracking permission)
- Approximate location derived from IP address
- Device type, operating system version, and language settings
- App usage and interaction data related to ads (such as ad impressions and clicks)

This information is collected and processed by Google, not by us, in accordance with [Google's Privacy Policy](https://policies.google.com/privacy) and Google's [User Consent Policy](https://www.google.com/about/company/user-consent-policy/). You can learn more about how Google uses information from apps that use its services at the links above.

## App Tracking Transparency

On iOS, the first time BrainWorkout may use tracking for personalized ads, you will see a system prompt asking for permission ("Allow Tracking"). If you decline, or if you disable tracking under **Settings > Privacy & Security > Tracking** on your device, BrainWorkout and its ad partners will not use your Advertising Identifier, and you will instead see non-personalized ads. You can change this choice at any time in your device settings.

## Children's Privacy

BrainWorkout is not directed at children under the age of 13, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us using the information below so we can address it.

## Data Retention and Your Choices

Because gameplay data is stored only on your device, you can remove it at any time by deleting the App or by clearing its data through your device settings. To limit ad tracking, use the App Tracking Transparency and ad personalization controls in your device's system settings.

## Security

We take reasonable measures to protect the App, but since we do not collect or store your gameplay data on any server, that data's security is governed by your own device's security settings.

## Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated "Last updated" date. Continued use of the App after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.

